Definition: a common language used by speakers of different languages
Example: Koine is a dialect of ancient Greek that was the lingua franca of the empire of Alexander the Great and was widely spoken throughout the eastern Mediterranean area in Roman times
Synonyms: interlanguage, koine, language, a, common, used, by, speakers, of, different, languages, Koine, is, dialect, ancient, Greek, that, was, the, lingua, franca, empire, Alexander, Great, and, widely, spoken, throughout, eastern, Mediterranean, area, in, Roman, times
Category: noun.communication
